comments.content:
It would help if there was some information on the origin of these numbers, e.g. rubber stamps.  
Except for the $ sign, they look similar to house numbers.  
Similar numbers are found in pre-WWI printers specimen books.  
As for digital versions various typewriter fonts have some similarity.  
 [See list at myfonts](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415143852/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/tag:typewriter/fonts/1-50/?sort=mob), and [see list at dafont](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415143852/http:/www.dafont.com/theme.php?cat=113&text=28035&fpp=50).  
Don
